<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4834</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Russian Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_TMI1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tereshchenko</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-21">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 21, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 22, midnight.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In taking over the direction of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, I
                                hasten to say to you how highly the whole Russian democracy is <pb facs="0149" n="75" xml:id="pg_75"/> inspired with the sentiment
                                of full solidarity with the great Republic which true to its
                                traditions of liberty has espoused the cause of the coalition for
                                the defense of justice and right. Like the United States,
                                emancipated Russia is not seeking conquest or any covetous end in
                                the present contest. The war is carried on to secure the freedom of
                                nations and achieve universal lasting peace effectively guaranteed
                                against all later attack. I am glad to find that those lofty
                                principles which were so eloquently formulated in America are
                                striking a warm unanimous echo in free Russia now mistress of her
                                destinies.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_TMI1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tereshchenko</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>